@page "/"

<PageTitle>FH6 Tuning Calculator</PageTitle>

@* Two-panel layout via the ported legacy .fh6-layout grid (minmax(320px,420px) 1fr, collapsing to
   one column at 880px) rather than MudGrid — this matches the legacy responsive breakpoint exactly
   (MudGrid's md collapse is 960px, which diverged in the 880–960px range). *@
<div class="fh6-layout">
    @* ===================== INPUTS (Car Setup) ===================== *@
    <section class="fh6-panel fh6-inputs" aria-label="Car inputs">
        <h2 class="fh6-panel-title">Car Setup</h2>
        @* Saved Setups first (legacy index.html: #setupsBlock is the first fieldset in the
           Car Setup panel, before Identity). *@
        <SavedSetupsBlock />
        <InputsPanel />
    </section>

    @* ===================== OUTPUTS (Recommended Tune) ===================== *@
    <section class="fh6-panel fh6-outputs" aria-label="Recommended tune">
        @* Goal tabs, compare/copy row, the two dials, summary strip, the nine cards, the
           "what changed" panel and the compare table — all driven by the engine through the
           shared CalculatorState (legacy refresh()). *@
        <OutputsPanel />
    </section>
</div>

<footer class="fh6-foot">
    <p>
        Forza Horizon 6 Tuning Calculator &mdash; values are math-derived starting points; fine-tune
        with telemetry in-game. Slider conventions follow the standard Forza tuning UI (FH4/FH5/FH6).
    </p>
</footer>

